    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-10-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-10-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="84"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                <head>84. Diary Entry by the President’s Assistant (<persName corresp="#p_HHR1"
                        >Haldeman</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d84fn1">Source:
                        National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential
                        Materials, White House Special Files, Handwritten Journals and Diaries of
                            <persName corresp="#p_HHR1">Harry Robbins Haldeman</persName>, Vol. 3,
                        September 29, 1969–January 12, 1970. No classification marking. The diary
                        entry, which is handwritten by <persName corresp="#p_HHR1"
                            >Haldeman</persName>, was transcribed by the editors.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1969-10-17">October 17, 1969</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion of <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName>’s
                    speech on Vietnam scheduled for November 3 and other matters unrelated to
                    national security policy.]</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">K[issinger]</persName> has all sorts of signal-type
                    activity going on around the world to try to jar Soviets and <gloss
                        target="#t_NVN1">NVN</gloss>—appears to be working because <persName
                        corresp="#p_DAF1">Dobrynin</persName> asked for early meeting—which we have
                    set secretly for Monday.<note n="2" xml:id="d84fn2">October 20.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">K</persName> thinks this is good chance of being the
                    big break, but that it will come in stages. P[resident] is more skeptical.</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion of matters unrelated to national security
                    policy.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
